What Speaker Pelosi and House Democrats assumed was their ace in the hole is, in fact, a dry hole. It turned out to be no more valuable to their months-long impeachment quest than yesterday’s dud of a call transcript.
His accounts were based on second-hand and even third-hand conversations, and with no supporting evidence whatsoever, cannot be considered anything more than hearsay.

Democrats overplayed their hand – they accepted a baseless, second-hand account of a phone call as gospel without even a brief consideration of the facts. After all the frenzy, we have exactly what we started with yesterday morning – nothing.
I’ve read the call transcript and ‘underwhelmed’ is an understatement – it contains nothing that warrants even the slightest thought of impeaching the President.

Following a drama-filled announcement yesterday that House Democrats would open an impeachment inquiry into President @realDonaldTrump, today’s news has predictably brought them crashing back to Earth.

It’s partisan politics at its finest and the American people are tired of it – it’s time to move on, accept the results of the election, and actually get to work on finding solutions to real, tangible problems facing Americans.

Speaker Pelosi and House Democrats chose to open an impeachment inquiry based on information they haven’t seen and a source they do not know. Just last week, they wanted to impeach Justice Kavanaugh, so this must be their latest ‘impeachment of the week.’
The facts simply don’t support their baseless accusations, but they aren’t concerned about that – they want to impeach @POTUS by any means necessary.

From the day President @realDonaldTrump was elected by the American people in 2016, Democrats have pursued every avenue they can think of to remove him from office – and even their most imaginative efforts have come up empty.
